1
00:03:26,214 --> 00:03:28,148
Why must you be this way?

2
00:03:28,216 --> 00:03:31,413
Why is there always a problem?
It's a good question.

3
00:03:33,287 --> 00:03:35,255
Do you want to go home?
Do you want to turn around?

4
00:03:35,323 --> 00:03:38,656
- Yes!
- It's the Himalayas!

5
00:03:38,726 --> 00:03:41,422
How long have I been talking
about the Himalayas?

6
00:03:41,496 --> 00:03:43,760
- How long?
- Far too long.

7
00:03:44,899 --> 00:03:48,733
Horst, when we get there,
can you give me a hand, please?

8
00:03:48,803 --> 00:03:51,897
- Yes, of course.
- Ingrid, stop it.

9
00:04:10,258 --> 00:04:13,694
Let's try to make the best of this.

10
00:04:16,264 --> 00:04:18,357
Where's thls idiot
who's supposed to meet us?

11
00:04:20,401 --> 00:04:21,459
Move!

12
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:26,971
Mr. Harrer.

13
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:28,702
I have your tickets.

14
00:04:28,776 --> 00:04:32,644
- I'm late. Take me to my train.
- No, you don't understand.

15
00:04:32,713 --> 00:04:36,114
I am Peter Aufschnaiter.
I am leading the expedition.

16
00:04:36,184 --> 00:04:38,277
- How do you do?
- Here's our celebrity!

17
00:04:38,352 --> 00:04:40,286
Mr. Harrer?

18
00:04:40,354 --> 00:04:44,313
May I say, Mr. Harrer,
on behalf of the Reichssportsfuhrer...

19
00:04:44,392 --> 00:04:47,589
we are honored to have
such a great German hero on the team.

20
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:50,130
Thank you, but I'm Austrian.

21
00:04:50,198 --> 00:04:52,564
Yes. but I'm sure that
.
as a distinguished member...

22
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:55,659
of the National Soclalist Party,
you would be proud to plant...

23
00:04:55,736 --> 00:05:00,730
our country's flag on the summit
of Nanga Parbat when you reach it.

24
00:05:00,808 --> 00:05:02,776
Hans Lobenhoffer.

25
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,436
Lutz Chicken.

26
00:05:07,348 --> 00:05:09,976
And a picture with your lovely wife.

27
00:05:14,322 --> 00:05:15,789
And Mr.--

28
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:18,792
Horst lmmendorf. Family frlend.
No plcture necessary.

29
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:24,130
When is the little one due.
.
Mrs. Harrer?

30
00:05:24,198 --> 00:05:26,689
About the time my husband
reaches the base camp.

31
00:05:28,302 --> 00:05:30,634
Thank you.

32
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:33,333
Why don't you tell the entire
stinking country our troubles?

33
00:05:35,109 --> 00:05:37,509
I'm getting on that traln.
Do you have anything you want to say?

34
00:05:41,549 --> 00:05:42,607
Fine.

35
00:05:43,818 --> 00:05:45,752
Go. Leave.

36
00:05:47,655 --> 00:05:50,146
I'll see you in four months.

37
00:05:52,059 --> 00:05:54,391
- Take good care of her, Horst.
- I will. Heinrich .
.

38
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:18,406
We will travel 5,000 miles.

39
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:21,073
When we reach lndia,
we will head for the Hlmalayas...

40
00:07:21,148 --> 00:07:24,083
and the ninth highest peak
on Earth, Nanga Parbat.

41
00:07:24,151 --> 00:07:27,643
Germany calls it "Unserberg--
Our Mountain. "

42
00:07:28,923 --> 00:07:31,858
Before us, four German expeditions
attempted it.

43
00:07:31,926 --> 00:07:33,484
All failed.

44
00:07:33,561 --> 00:07:37,224
Eleven climbers were killed
in storms and avalanches.

45
00:07:37,298 --> 00:07:41,860
By now, the conquest of Nanga Parbat
is a national obsession--

46
00:07:41,936 --> 00:07:44,302
a matter of German pride.

47
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:52,235
July 29, 1939.

48
00:07:52,313 --> 00:07:56,147
We have already made Camp Four
at 22.000 feet.
.

49
00:07:56,217 --> 00:08:01,211
Overhead is the Reklak Glacier
and a difficult climb up the icefall.

50
00:08:04,325 --> 00:08:06,919
The baby must be
at least one month old now.

51
00:08:08,562 --> 00:08:11,861
I have been
so confused and dlstracted.

52
00:08:11,932 --> 00:08:14,730
I can 't climb
with my usual confldence.

53
00:08:41,362 --> 00:08:43,523
Are you all right?

54
00:08:48,869 --> 00:08:50,461
Shit!

55
00:08:52,239 --> 00:08:55,902
- Are you al I right?
- Shall we come down?

56
00:08:58,212 --> 00:09:00,009
Lost a crampon !

57
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,810
Go ahead!

58
00:09:24,405 --> 00:09:27,135
The weather's getting bad.
We should rope up.

59
00:09:28,742 --> 00:09:34,180
- Did you hurt yourself back there?
- Just a scratch. I'll lead.

60
00:10:03,777 --> 00:10:05,642
Rocks!

61
00:10:05,713 --> 00:10:08,045
Look out below!

62
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:18,758
Hold me!

63
00:10:31,305 --> 00:10:33,239
Have you got me?

64
00:10:42,283 --> 00:10:44,217
Hold me!

65
00:11:46,046 --> 00:11:48,412
You should have told me
how bad that wound was.

66
00:11:49,183 --> 00:11:52,152
I should take a look at lt.
I could sew it up.

67
00:11:57,157 --> 00:11:58,886
It's not your problem.

68
00:12:01,895 --> 00:12:03,829
Actually, it is my problem.

69
00:12:03,897 --> 00:12:07,025
- It's my life.
- What?

70
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:10,730
When you conceal a serious injury
and put my life at risk...

71
00:12:10,804 --> 00:12:12,772
I consider th at my problem.

72
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:15,934
No, you put your life at rlsk.
I saved it, so shut up !

73
00:12:16,010 --> 00:12:18,205
Please, it is not your place--

74
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,871
Shut up !

75
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:24,345
The next time you lle
about an lnjury, Heinrich...

76
00:12:25,319 --> 00:12:27,253
you're off the team.

77
00:12:30,591 --> 00:12:32,388
Try it.

78
00:13:52,906 --> 00:13:56,637
August 4th, Camp Five.
Some fierce storms have passed.

79
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:59,702
My teammates are nervous
about the avalanches...

80
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:02,248
so we 've been holed up for days.

81
00:14:02,316 --> 00:14:06,548
Aufschnalter should take advantage of
this lowland weather to make high camp.

82
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:10,283
But he disagrees with me. Fool.

83
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:15,328
It seems the others don 't mind
sitting here waiting...

84
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:18,160
hoping, doing nothing.

85
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:22,965
So much time to question
one 's self is not good.

86
00:14:25,539 --> 00:14:28,531
I am beginnlng to think
this whole expedition was a mistake.

87
00:14:47,127 --> 00:14:49,061
Run ! Avalanche! Get out!

88
00:14:54,168 --> 00:14:55,362
Leave everything!

89
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:12,084
Put that down !

90
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,049
We are going down now!

91
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:17,989
If they're frightened of a storm,
send them down to Camp Two.

92
00:15:18,058 --> 00:15:21,391
I could summit on my own !
Always give the best man his shot!

93
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:23,953
He's trying to tell us
he's the best man.

94
00:15:24,031 --> 00:15:26,261
Give me two Sherpas.
I can make Camp Six by tonight...

95
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,267
and my final attack tomorrow!

96
00:15:28,335 --> 00:15:31,304
- We are going down now as a team!
- I've earned that peak!

97
00:15:31,371 --> 00:15:33,305
- I want th at peak!
- As a team! That's an order!

98
00:15:33,373 --> 00:15:36,934
That is an order! An order!

99
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:39,737
Follow me!

100
00:16:41,975 --> 00:16:45,103
Dalai Lama photo. Good protection.

101
00:16:45,178 --> 00:16:48,045
Take it. Si Hib.
.
It will protect you.

102
00:16:48,115 --> 00:16:51,482
No, that means nothing to me.

103
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:54,180
Dalai Lama. Dalai Lama photo.

104
00:16:54,254 --> 00:16:56,017
Si Hib, take it.

105
00:16:56,089 --> 00:16:58,023
Good protection for you.

106
00:17:11,738 --> 00:17:14,332
Good afternoon, Herr Harrer.

107
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:16,569
Well, let's hope that Germany
retreats from Poland...

108
00:17:16,643 --> 00:17:18,838
as quickly as you did
from your mountain.

109
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:21,380
It might save you some prison time.

110
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:25,084
What is this? Who are you?

111
00:17:25,152 --> 00:17:30,180
- I'm sorry, but you're under arrest.
- What charge? Failure to summit?

112
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:31,724
I'm afraid not.

113
00:17:32,893 --> 00:17:37,057
You see, war has been declared between
Hls Majesty's Government and Germany.

114
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:42,193
So all enemy aliens on British Empire
soil are now prisoners of war.

115
00:18:25,979 --> 00:18:28,914
- Stop, or I'll shoot!
- Hands up!

116
00:18:28,982 --> 00:18:31,644
No, you don't understand!
I'm Austrian ! I'm a cllmber!

117
00:18:31,718 --> 00:18:34,949
I have nothing to do
with your silly war!

118
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:44,055
I can walk myself.
This is an insult!

119
00:18:45,899 --> 00:18:48,925
You think you have the last word,
but you don't!

120
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:51,766
Pigs! All of you, pigs!

121
00:19:05,252 --> 00:19:07,186
October 15, 1939.

122
00:19:09,956 --> 00:19:12,857
Reaching prison camp,
I make a promise to myself.

123
00:19:14,728 --> 00:19:18,960
I will be lying beside lngrid before
the summer solstice of the new year.

124
00:19:20,867 --> 00:19:23,392
The Hlmalayas are right in front of us.

125
00:19:23,470 --> 00:19:26,439
It will be easy to escape
and get lost in them.

126
00:19:39,319 --> 00:19:42,880
My fourth escape attempt
brings me no closer to my goal.

127
00:19:43,957 --> 00:19:46,323
How far did you get this time?

128
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:50,329
All I have achieved is a certaln
dubious celebrity among the prisoners.

129
00:20:15,222 --> 00:20:18,988
If only my hand could express
what is ln my heart.

130
00:20:33,507 --> 00:20:35,771
I hear the guards
are mailing letters for you.

131
00:20:36,977 --> 00:20:38,171
Yes.

132
00:20:38,245 --> 00:20:40,713
Would you mail these?

133
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:45,683
Thank you.

134
00:20:45,752 --> 00:20:48,118
Hey, Heinrich, have you read this book?

135
00:20:48,188 --> 00:20:50,554
It was checked out to you.

136
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:58,765
- We need to talk to you.
- What about?

137
00:20:58,832 --> 00:21:00,299
About this.

138
00:21:08,809 --> 00:21:11,710
Impressive. When do you plan to leave?

139
00:21:11,778 --> 00:21:13,803
After monsoon season. And you?

140
00:21:15,615 --> 00:21:19,711
I see you've chosen
my route through Tibet.

141
00:21:19,786 --> 00:21:23,722
The few foreigners who have tried
never came back. So, good luck.

142
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:27,055
- Would you like to come with us?
- Why?

143
00:21:27,127 --> 00:21:30,290
After all, you are the authority
on jailbreak around here.

144
00:21:30,363 --> 00:21:33,924
- We could benefit from your experience.
- Please.

145
00:21:35,569 --> 00:21:37,833
Stop this embarrassing charade.

146
00:21:39,306 --> 00:21:43,140
Every time you escape,
the patrols are doubled and tripled.

147
00:21:43,210 --> 00:21:46,475
It is making life very difficult
for the rest of us.

148
00:21:46,546 --> 00:21:49,606
I prefer to travel on my own,
but thanks for thinking of me.

149
00:21:58,291 --> 00:22:00,225
The mailman has come.

150
00:22:39,032 --> 00:22:40,624
Dear Heinrlch:

151
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:44,397
Please sign the enclosed dlvorce papers
and send them to my lawyer.

152
00:22:44,471 --> 00:22:48,532
Horst and I intend to be married
as soon as the divorce is flnalized.

153
00:22:48,608 --> 00:22:50,542
As for your letter, yes.

154
00:22:50,610 --> 00:22:54,569
Your son, Rolf Harrer, was born
while you were climbing the mountain.

155
00:22:54,648 --> 00:22:58,584
He is now two years old
and calls Horst "papa. "

156
00:22:58,652 --> 00:23:00,847
When he is old enough,
I will tell him...

157
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:03,549
his real father was lost
in the Himalayas.

158
00:23:03,623 --> 00:23:05,682
It seems the kindest thing
to say consldering...

159
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:08,227
you never wanted the child anyway.

160
00:23:08,295 --> 00:23:10,855
Needless to say,
I have no intention...

161
00:23:10,931 --> 00:23:14,662
of "resolving our differences "
as you suggested.

162
00:23:14,734 --> 00:23:18,192
They were resolved
the moment you left Austria.

163
00:23:18,271 --> 00:23:21,434
I'm sorry you have been
imprisoned ln lndia...

164
00:23:21,508 --> 00:23:25,706
and hope this dreadful war will soon
be over for everyone's sake.

165
00:23:25,779 --> 00:23:27,371
Ingrid.

166
00:24:55,502 --> 00:24:56,833
I'm coming with you.

167
00:25:05,612 --> 00:25:07,079
This is your plan?

168
00:25:11,117 --> 00:25:14,245
In my humble opinion,
this is ridiculous.

169
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:17,187
Then since you are so humble,
we won't ask your opinion.

170
00:26:02,802 --> 00:26:05,032
Open the charts. Turn around.

171
00:26:05,105 --> 00:26:09,007
Keep your back to the gate.
Open the charts!

172
00:26:24,324 --> 00:26:27,521
Keep talking. Wait for my signal.

173
00:26:28,628 --> 00:26:30,653
We are clear. Okay.

174
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:45,702
Open the gates!

175
00:26:53,386 --> 00:26:56,947
See to this. Open the gates!

176
00:27:32,125 --> 00:27:34,093
I'm going off on my own.

177
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,219
So, good luck.

178
00:28:11,831 --> 00:28:17,701
First escape from prlson camp,
November 18, 1939.

179
00:28:17,770 --> 00:28:20,898
Rolf Harrer--
three and a half months old.

180
00:28:23,209 --> 00:28:27,270
My 30th birthday, July 6, 1941.

181
00:28:27,347 --> 00:28:32,182
Rolf Harrer-- exactly one year,
11 months and 26 days.

182
00:28:34,621 --> 00:28:38,022
Last escape from Dehra Dun.
Rolf Harrer--

183
00:31:06,272 --> 00:31:10,504
Take two and sleep it off.
I'll send you a bill in the morning.

184
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:16,514
What are you doing here?

185
00:31:16,582 --> 00:31:21,747
I missed you so much.
I thought I'd pay you a visit.

186
00:31:25,725 --> 00:31:28,159
What about the others?

187
00:31:28,227 --> 00:31:30,855
The ltalians were caught
outside Nelang.

188
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:33,990
Lutz and Hans got sick
and had to turn back.

189
00:31:36,035 --> 00:31:39,027
- Sorry to hear that.
- I'm sure you're heartbroken.

190
00:31:41,674 --> 00:31:45,633
May I impose upon your generous nature
and camp here tonight?

191
00:31:45,711 --> 00:31:47,645
Be my guest.

192
00:31:47,713 --> 00:31:50,910
Thank you.
It is very gracious of you.

193
00:32:11,370 --> 00:32:13,304
- Good.
- What else do you have in there?

194
00:32:13,372 --> 00:32:15,602
A ten-piece orchestra?

195
00:32:15,675 --> 00:32:20,078
By the way, I heard
the Japanese have retreated...

196
00:32:20,146 --> 00:32:24,173
all the way back to Shanghai so even
if you make it to the Chinese border...

197
00:32:24,250 --> 00:32:26,241
you may have dlfficulty
catchlng up with them.

198
00:32:26,319 --> 00:32:28,947
I don 't care if they're repelled
all the way back to Tokyo.

199
00:32:29,021 --> 00:32:31,012
You should if you want
to get back to Austria.

200
00:32:31,991 --> 00:32:34,152
- But I don't.
- Don't what?

201
00:32:36,462 --> 00:32:39,158
- Plan to go back.
- Why not?

202
00:32:42,401 --> 00:32:45,336
No particular reason.

203
00:32:45,404 --> 00:32:47,201
When you get there, tell my wife...

204
00:32:47,273 --> 00:32:51,300
that two years in prison camp is roughly
equivalent to four years of marriage.

205
00:32:51,377 --> 00:32:53,937
And I'm glad to be free of them both.

206
00:32:56,949 --> 00:33:01,181
I'm not golng back either,
not until this shameful war is over.

207
00:33:01,254 --> 00:33:03,984
- And where are you headed?
- Tibet.

208
00:33:04,056 --> 00:33:08,652
Then on to China.
.
see if I can find some work there.

209
00:33:09,829 --> 00:33:11,194
And you ?

210
00:33:11,264 --> 00:33:15,724
By my calculations, the Chinese border
is 2,058 kilometers away.

211
00:33:15,801 --> 00:33:18,395
Tibet is 68.

212
00:33:18,471 --> 00:33:22,635
It's a long way to travel
with such a heavy load.

213
00:33:23,743 --> 00:33:26,109
No, just full of food.

214
00:33:26,178 --> 00:33:28,976
- Precisely.
- Mine.

215
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:32,308
That's too bad.

216
00:33:32,385 --> 00:33:36,219
Those mountains are treacherous.
There are glaciers to be crossed.

217
00:33:36,289 --> 00:33:38,484
If you had roped up to me,
I could have kept you alive.

218
00:33:38,558 --> 00:33:40,890
Considering your performance
the last time we roped up...

219
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:43,155
I think I'm safer without you.

220
00:33:47,466 --> 00:33:48,728
Of course.

221
00:33:53,105 --> 00:33:57,405
But I think you are wrong about
that Tibetan border calculatlon.

222
00:33:57,476 --> 00:34:00,673
By my measurements,
it is 65 kilometers.

223
00:34:03,916 --> 00:34:05,850
Care to wager a kilo of food on that?

224
00:34:08,754 --> 00:34:12,690
All you've got is some stale crackers.

225
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:16,856
But I'm right. I'll win.

226
00:34:58,437 --> 00:35:01,270
Tibet, the roof of the world.

227
00:35:01,340 --> 00:35:04,468
It feels as though we have
ascended a medieval stone fortress...

228
00:35:04,543 --> 00:35:07,376
towering above the center of Asla.

229
00:35:07,446 --> 00:35:09,937
This ls the highest country on Earth.

230
00:35:10,016 --> 00:35:11,950
And the most isolated.

231
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:22,484
There it is.

232
00:35:23,529 --> 00:35:25,429
Tibet.

233
00:35:26,599 --> 00:35:30,262
- Exactly 68 kilometers.
- Congratulations.

234
00:35:31,637 --> 00:35:33,935
Unfortunately, you've eaten
all your winnings.

235
00:35:52,058 --> 00:35:53,286
Yes.

236
00:35:53,359 --> 00:35:56,328
Just smile and say yes.
It's better that way.

237
00:35:59,932 --> 00:36:02,127
It's amazing what you learn
in prison, isn't it?

238
00:36:12,011 --> 00:36:13,569
Tibet.

239
00:36:16,282 --> 00:36:18,876
- No foreigners allowed in Tlbet.
- Oh, please!

240
00:36:18,951 --> 00:36:20,475
No foreigner!

241
00:36:20,553 --> 00:36:22,544
Oh, please!

242
00:36:29,695 --> 00:36:32,858
Yes. Thank you. Of course.

243
00:37:00,426 --> 00:37:02,394
No translation needed.

244
00:37:33,959 --> 00:37:36,257
Some people are glad to see us.

245
00:37:36,328 --> 00:37:38,626
